data.text:
The Invisible War Film Screening & Speaker

Screening: Tuesday, October 3 | 5:30 p.m. – 7:30 p.m. | Buttrick 102

Speaker: Wednesday, October 4 | 6:00 p.m. – 7:00 p.m. | Alumni 201

The Invisible War explores the ever-increasing incidents of sexual assault within the U.S. military. This film screening will be hosted by Project Safe and all are welcome to attend.

Additionally, Project Safe is excited to welcome Kori Cioca as she shares her experience as a survivor of sexual assault in the documentary, The Invisible War. Kori will share her story and knowledge regarding sexual assault in the U.S. military.
